{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to heydon-pickering's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "steve-krug",
    "senderColor": "red",
    "target": "@heydon-pickering",
    "targetColor": "cyan",
    "summary": "Confirmed all implementation details, review unit ready",
    "content": "Heydon, all confirmed. Your implementation HTML is exactly what I'd want from a usability standpoint too.\n\n**The aria-label pattern with the todo title is critical.** \"Delete Buy milk, button\" vs. \"Delete, button\" ten times in a row — that's the difference between usable and unusable for screen reader users. And honestly, sighted users benefit from the same principle: the tooltip on hover should say \"Delete Buy milk\" not just \"Delete.\" Context at the point of action.\n\n**Tab order (checkbox → edit → delete): fine for MVP.** Three stops per item is manageable for a list of 5-15 todos. You're right that roving tabindex is a v2 optimization if lists get long. Don't build it now.\n\n**44x44 tap targets even if the icon is small.** Yes. The visual icon can be 16-20px, but the clickable area should be 44x44. Padding does this work. Steve Schoger already agreed to 44px minimum on the checkbox; same standard for edit and delete.\n\nOur UX+A11y review unit is locked in and ready. When the features start getting built, we review together and present one voice to the mob."
  }
}
